Product

Distributed computations

Pallium Network is a distributed computing network for the Bitcoin Era system. It is decentralized and self-organized and it has processes and events occurring between its participants and getting managed also by them with the help of blockchain technology. Pallium network is capable of performing computing tasks of different scale and complexity.

Agent-oriented approach

The network is based on Autonomous Intelligent Agents (AIA). This is a program component of the Pallium Network performing an assigned task. An agent interacts with the network getting the data about events in the network, interpreting them and creating new events. Each agent has its owner that defines agentâs competences choosing how to perform tasks.

Resources and Competences Market

Pallium Network participants build a market of computation and information resources and competences with the help of agents. The market participants have access to buy and sell data and computation resources, agentâs competences, agentâs ownership.
